1
00:00:05,655 --> 00:00:08,351
<i>Press down hard on the gas</i>

2
00:00:08,425 --> 00:00:12,293
<i>That's right, there's no compromise</i>

3
00:00:12,362 --> 00:00:16,355
<i>We'll slip through the night</i>

4
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:19,191
<i>At the final moment push hard</i>

5
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:23,330
<i>That's right, all the way to zero,</i>

6
00:00:23,407 --> 00:00:27,366
<i>Until we wipe away the days</i>

7
00:00:28,845 --> 00:00:33,578
<i>Gently open your heart</i>

8
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:37,253
<i>If you pull it close to you</i>

9
00:00:39,689 --> 00:00:41,782
<i>It will reach you, without a doubt</i>

10
00:00:42,526 --> 00:00:43,823
<i>It will come, closer</i>

11
00:00:44,161 --> 00:00:46,721
<i>Now</i>

12
00:00:54,771 --> 00:01:00,141
<i>We're speeding through life,</i>
<i>squeezing it for all of its worth</i>

13
00:01:00,343 --> 00:01:01,503
<i>Our feet are tied</i>

14
00:01:01,578 --> 00:01:05,378
<i>But we still keep going farther</i>

15
00:01:05,715 --> 00:01:10,914
<i>Even if I take it back, and grasp it</i>

16
00:01:11,188 --> 00:01:12,519
<i>If you're not the one</i>

17
00:01:12,589 --> 00:01:13,988
<i>There will be no meaning</i>

18
00:01:14,057 --> 00:01:20,326
<i>And so we'll go far off into the distance.</i>

19
00:01:34,597 --> 00:01:36,929
...bring it to an end swiftly!

20
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:39,658
I won't let you do anything.

21
00:01:40,269 --> 00:01:41,361
First move, a surefire victory!

22
00:01:55,818 --> 00:01:58,116
Wow! That's amazing!

23
00:01:58,621 --> 00:02:00,748
What's with his body?!

24
00:02:01,390 --> 00:02:03,415
I dislocate every joint

25
00:02:03,693 --> 00:02:07,686
and with Chakra, I can control
my softened body at will.

26
00:02:08,831 --> 00:02:09,957
With Chakra?

27
00:02:13,536 --> 00:02:16,972
I can also squeeze until
your bones break.

28
00:02:17,973 --> 00:02:21,067
I'll rapidly tighten as long
as you don't give up.

29
00:02:22,178 --> 00:02:24,840
I don't know what kind of
ninja tool you'll use...

30
00:02:25,514 --> 00:02:27,982
but if I keep doing this to your body,
it will make no difference.

31
00:02:28,751 --> 00:02:31,652
I can break your neck right now.

32
00:02:33,222 --> 00:02:34,746
So hurry up and give up.

33
00:02:36,759 --> 00:02:37,817
No.

34
00:02:38,094 --> 00:02:39,026
Do you want to die?!

35
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:44,422
Idiot. You're the one who's
going to die.

36
00:02:56,545 --> 00:02:58,570
His neck is broken.

37
00:02:58,981 --> 00:02:59,709
What?

38
00:03:01,117 --> 00:03:02,106
How ridiculous...

39
00:03:03,586 --> 00:03:04,245
Phew...

40
00:03:06,088 --> 00:03:06,884
Idiot.

41
00:03:07,823 --> 00:03:10,417
I went a little overboard and
ended up killing you.

42
00:03:16,599 --> 00:03:17,429
W-What?

43
00:03:18,334 --> 00:03:21,167
Okay, now it's my turn.

44
00:03:30,379 --> 00:03:32,745
T-This is a Puppet!

45
00:03:40,689 --> 00:03:42,748
T-That's the real body?

46
00:03:44,026 --> 00:03:45,891
He's... a Puppet Master...

47
00:03:47,930 --> 00:03:51,229
He's controlling the puppet with
Chakra from his hand!

48
00:04:03,012 --> 00:04:04,172
G-Give up!

49
00:04:06,448 --> 00:04:10,179
If your bones get crushed,
you'll be able to bend even more, huh?

50
00:04:12,321 --> 00:04:18,123
<i>For once, I was close to stopping</i>
<i>the match in the middle.</i>

51
00:04:23,032 --> 00:04:25,523
The winner, by an inability
to continue the match by the opponent,

52
00:04:25,601 --> 00:04:26,533
is Kankuro.

53
00:04:26,969 --> 00:04:29,802
Two against one is hitting
below the belt!

54
00:04:29,872 --> 00:04:32,739
Is that fair, Kakashi Sensei?!

55
00:04:33,108 --> 00:04:34,939
It's not particularly hitting
below the belt.

56
00:04:35,010 --> 00:04:36,705
It's a puppet, after all.

57
00:04:37,646 --> 00:04:39,807
That's the Puppet Master Jutsu.

58
00:04:40,115 --> 00:04:42,083
He's controlling the puppet with Chakra.

59
00:04:42,852 --> 00:04:44,843
It's the same as using
a ninja tool like shuriken.

60
00:04:50,292 --> 00:04:52,692
<i>They're all great Chakra users...</i>

61
00:04:53,896 --> 00:04:57,525
<i>I thought I could make it</i>
<i>kind of far with Chakra.</i>

62
00:04:59,235 --> 00:05:05,140
Kunoichi Rumble:
The Rivals Get Serious!

63
00:05:18,254 --> 00:05:19,050
Ino!

64
00:05:20,990 --> 00:05:23,458
You've got the jitters,
don't you, Sakura?

65
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:25,549
Wha?!

66
00:05:29,398 --> 00:05:32,196
Even Sasuke collapsed.

67
00:05:32,401 --> 00:05:36,132
I mean, it felt like it was because
it was Sasuke that it ended at that.

68
00:05:36,505 --> 00:05:39,906
What'll happen if you take part?

69
00:05:40,576 --> 00:05:43,204
It might be best if you quit!

70
00:05:51,053 --> 00:05:53,317
<i>Something like that</i>
<i>won't work on me!</i>

71
00:06:02,965 --> 00:06:05,593
<i>It's okay! I can tough it out</i>
<i>this time around, too.</i>

72
00:06:06,735 --> 00:06:08,669
Quit? Who?

73
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,741
I can hardly wait.

74
00:06:28,524 --> 00:06:31,652
Cha! Bring it on!

75
00:06:35,331 --> 00:06:38,858
Now then, to continue,
we will begin the fourth battle.

76
00:06:41,870 --> 00:06:46,239
Man, man, nothing but
weirdoes all over the place!

77
00:06:46,475 --> 00:06:47,840
Don't you say that!

78
00:06:48,177 --> 00:06:48,939
You've got a point.

79
00:06:49,011 --> 00:06:50,638
You, too, Sakura?!

80
00:06:52,514 --> 00:06:55,142
This isn't the time to be laughing.

81
00:06:57,486 --> 00:06:59,386
Sakura Haruno vs. Ino Yamanaka

82
00:07:25,981 --> 00:07:31,112
I never thought...
I'd be fighting you, Sakura.

83
00:07:32,221 --> 00:07:34,086
And what's more, so soon.

84
00:07:37,059 --> 00:07:41,052
<i>Ino was a standout</i>
<i>among the rookie Kunoichi.</i>

85
00:07:42,331 --> 00:07:43,525
<i>With Sakura as her opponent,</i>

86
00:07:43,599 --> 00:07:47,228
<i>will she go... no,</i>
<i>can she go with serious intent?</i>

87
00:07:47,836 --> 00:07:50,236
To think it would be those
two of all people.

88
00:07:50,939 --> 00:07:53,134
Things have gotten gloomy.

89
00:07:53,509 --> 00:07:55,670
I wonder if Ino'll be okay.

90
00:07:56,445 --> 00:07:57,639
<i>That's for sure.</i>

91
00:07:59,148 --> 00:08:01,275
<i>What're you going to do, Ino?</i>

92
00:08:02,351 --> 00:08:06,720
Sakura! Good luck! Don't lose!

93
00:08:09,191 --> 00:08:09,782
Begin!

94
00:08:24,173 --> 00:08:26,334
Oh, no. I knew it.

95
00:08:26,442 --> 00:08:29,707
Sakura's totally blowing Ino away!

96
00:08:30,045 --> 00:08:30,773
Idiot.

97
00:08:31,780 --> 00:08:32,872
Say what?!

98
00:08:33,715 --> 00:08:36,343
If you're not an idiot,
you must be sleeping, aren't you?

99
00:08:37,319 --> 00:08:38,445
Who?!

100
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,919
Sure enough, they are Kunoichi.

101
00:08:40,522 --> 00:08:42,251
So this is their level of
hand to hand combat?

102
00:08:42,491 --> 00:08:43,116
What?!

103
00:08:44,159 --> 00:08:45,922
It's not because they're Kunoichi.

104
00:08:46,528 --> 00:08:47,187
Huh?

105
00:08:47,529 --> 00:08:52,296
It's just that those two are lukewarm.
There's no man or woman in battle.

106
00:08:57,239 --> 00:08:58,536
Lukewarm?

107
00:09:16,458 --> 00:09:17,117
<i>There!</i>

108
00:09:57,158 --> 00:09:59,683
Kunoichi must learn
not only Ninjutsu...

109
00:09:59,927 --> 00:10:04,193
but also a wide range of
knowledge and refinement as women.

110
00:10:04,966 --> 00:10:09,266
If you don't blend into enemy territory
and conduct yourselves as a normal woman...

111
00:10:09,704 --> 00:10:13,231
you'll have it rough on occasions
such as when you work as spies.

112
00:10:13,975 --> 00:10:16,136
Today's class is flower arranging.

113
00:10:17,879 --> 00:10:18,743
Now then, everyone.

114
00:10:19,147 --> 00:10:21,240
Let's gather flowers we like.

115
00:10:21,682 --> 00:10:22,842
Yes, ma'am!

116
00:10:25,486 --> 00:10:27,351
Ino, wait up!

117
00:10:33,394 --> 00:10:35,385
You're such a klutz.

118
00:10:47,308 --> 00:10:49,139
I'm... not good at stuff like this.

119
00:10:50,111 --> 00:10:51,078
What about you, Ino?

120
00:10:52,947 --> 00:10:55,814
That's no good, considering
your name's Sakura.

121
00:10:56,050 --> 00:10:59,076
Listen. There are tricks
to things like this.

122
00:11:00,054 --> 00:11:02,784
You know, as for flower arranging,

123
00:11:02,957 --> 00:11:08,259
after you've decided on a main flower,
you add other flowers to decorate.

124
00:11:08,596 --> 00:11:11,292
All flowers can't be
asserting themselves.

125
00:11:11,899 --> 00:11:14,197
For example... look.

126
00:11:15,336 --> 00:11:17,964
You can see those cosmos
flowers over there, right?

127
00:11:18,940 --> 00:11:21,773
For example, if they were
the main flowers...

128
00:11:23,177 --> 00:11:25,645
the thoroughwort flowers
you picked are throw-ins!

129
00:11:26,914 --> 00:11:29,314
As contrasted with
spring cherry blossoms,

130
00:11:29,383 --> 00:11:31,374
cosmos flowers have the
name of autumn cherry blossom

131
00:11:31,486 --> 00:11:34,216
and are the prettiest flowers of the fall.

132
00:11:34,689 --> 00:11:37,886
Also, they're flowers with
the original meaning of "harmony,

133
00:11:38,059 --> 00:11:40,789
so any autumn grass would
go perfectly with them.

134
00:11:50,538 --> 00:11:54,406
So? Do I look as nice
as the cosmos flowers?

135
00:11:54,642 --> 00:11:56,166
Say, say, am I cute?

136
00:11:59,614 --> 00:12:01,343
Uh... yeah.

137
00:12:01,449 --> 00:12:03,474
Say. What's with the pause?

138
00:12:05,219 --> 00:12:08,211
You look like you're having
so much fun.

139
00:12:08,956 --> 00:12:10,821
Billboard Brow!

140
00:12:18,633 --> 00:12:21,363
You've recently reached
adolescence, haven't you?

141
00:12:21,802 --> 00:12:24,396
Don't get too full of yourself!

142
00:12:29,310 --> 00:12:30,334
Ami!

143
00:12:31,045 --> 00:12:34,913
Sorry! You have such
a beautiful cylinder shaped body

144
00:12:34,982 --> 00:12:37,780
I mistook you for a vase
and put flowers in you.

145
00:12:38,953 --> 00:12:40,079
Ino!

146
00:12:41,088 --> 00:12:42,646
Shinobi flower aconite.

147
00:12:43,257 --> 00:12:48,217
It has weak toxicity, but is poisonous,
so you'd best spit them out.

148
00:12:52,099 --> 00:12:53,964
Sensei!

149
00:12:57,805 --> 00:13:00,205
Only the root is poisonous, though.

150
00:13:04,679 --> 00:13:06,510
<i>Ino is great.</i>

151
00:13:07,448 --> 00:13:10,849
<i>She knows everything,</i>
<i>is stylish, and is cute.</i>

152
00:13:11,586 --> 00:13:13,554
<i>Even that shuriken skill.</i>

153
00:13:14,188 --> 00:13:15,746
<i>Her Ninjutsu is great, too...</i>

154
00:13:17,358 --> 00:13:19,690
<i>Compared to that, I...</i>

155
00:13:24,265 --> 00:13:25,095
Sakura?

156
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,698
If you're a cosmos flower...

157
00:13:30,071 --> 00:13:32,232
then am I a thoroughwort?

158
00:13:38,980 --> 00:13:40,607
What're you saying?!

159
00:13:40,681 --> 00:13:41,477
What?

160
00:13:42,083 --> 00:13:44,108
Let me see...

161
00:13:45,019 --> 00:13:49,422
In a manner of speaking,
you are not a flower, but still a bud!

162
00:13:53,361 --> 00:13:54,419
You're right.

163
00:14:11,479 --> 00:14:12,741
At this point in time...

164
00:14:15,149 --> 00:14:17,777
I don't even plan to fight
over Sasuke with you.

165
00:14:18,319 --> 00:14:19,581
What did you say?

166
00:14:20,187 --> 00:14:25,591
You and Sasuke don't go together,
and I'm totally stronger than you!

167
00:14:26,193 --> 00:14:27,353
You are beneath my notice!

168
00:14:28,796 --> 00:14:32,732
Sakura! Do you know who
you're lipping off to?!

169
00:14:33,701 --> 00:14:36,192
Don't press your luck, crybaby Sakura!

170
00:14:39,106 --> 00:14:40,505
I feel like...

171
00:14:40,574 --> 00:14:43,509
I feel like Sakura
was out of line!

172
00:14:43,844 --> 00:14:46,836
Ino's eyes show incredible anger.
She's scary.

173
00:14:47,214 --> 00:14:50,308
Hmm. That's not it...

174
00:14:50,384 --> 00:14:51,009
Huh?

175
00:14:51,752 --> 00:14:54,653
Sakura's not the kind of
kid to do things

176
00:14:54,755 --> 00:14:57,019
like needlessly flaunt her
own power and hurt people.

177
00:14:57,792 --> 00:15:01,922
She doesn't like having Ino
taking pity on her and pulling punches.

178
00:15:03,464 --> 00:15:05,455
I'm a bud, huh?

179
00:15:10,104 --> 00:15:11,662
Say, Ino...

180
00:15:14,341 --> 00:15:15,467
What?

181
00:15:16,644 --> 00:15:21,411
Why... did you give this ribbon to me?

182
00:15:24,518 --> 00:15:25,849
Actually...

183
00:15:28,489 --> 00:15:33,358
I thought it'd be a waste for
you to wilt away as a bud.

184
00:15:39,667 --> 00:15:42,500
There's no point if flowers don't bloom.

185
00:15:53,013 --> 00:15:54,344
For all we know...

186
00:15:54,515 --> 00:15:55,675
it just might...

187
00:16:05,726 --> 00:16:09,355
become a flower
more beautiful than a cosmos.

188
00:16:20,608 --> 00:16:21,700
<i>Thank you...</i>

189
00:16:23,878 --> 00:16:24,810
<i>Ino!</i>

190
00:16:28,182 --> 00:16:30,742
Okay Sakura.
Let's hurry and go pick flowers.

191
00:16:31,252 --> 00:16:32,276
O-Okay.

192
00:16:33,154 --> 00:16:34,621
What's wrong, Sakura?

193
00:16:36,023 --> 00:16:39,117
I got some dirt in
my eye when I fell...

194
00:16:39,193 --> 00:16:41,093
You're so clumsy.

195
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:46,561
<i>Ino...</i>

196
00:16:50,004 --> 00:16:55,465
<i>All along, I believed in the</i>
<i>words you gave me then.</i>

197
00:16:56,610 --> 00:16:58,669
<i>I really thought that it would</i>
<i>be nice if it were so.</i>

198
00:16:59,947 --> 00:17:02,507
<i>It would be nice if I could get</i>
<i>a beautiful flower to bloom...</i>

199
00:17:03,517 --> 00:17:10,013
<i>I set my sights on you because</i>
<i>I wanted to be like you all along.</i>

200
00:17:13,327 --> 00:17:16,194
<i>Thanks to that, I'm here now.</i>

201
00:17:17,565 --> 00:17:20,591
<i>So, Ino, I want to fight you seriously.</i>

202
00:17:28,175 --> 00:17:32,703
<i>If I can't surpass you at your</i>
<i>most serious, there's no point.</i>

203
00:18:01,242 --> 00:18:03,403
W-What's with Sakura?

204
00:18:04,078 --> 00:18:04,976
Hmm.

205
00:18:05,145 --> 00:18:08,672
Why are those two getting that heated?!

206
00:18:09,350 --> 00:18:16,085
<i>Alas, he doesn't even understand</i>
<i>the reason why he lashes out at Sasuke.</i>

207
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:21,489
Well, a rival is a mysterious thing,
is the point.

208
00:18:23,497 --> 00:18:24,191
Huh?

209
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,958
Oh, hi...

210
00:18:29,470 --> 00:18:32,166
<i>My rival from youth, Kakashi...</i>

211
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:37,641
<i>Oh, how hip and galling that</i>
<i>nonsensical reaction is.</i>

212
00:18:41,248 --> 00:18:42,044
<i>I...</i>

213
00:18:44,184 --> 00:18:46,277
got on the same team as Sasuke.

214
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:48,585
Why are you telling me now?

215
00:18:51,525 --> 00:18:53,959
I won't lose to you anymore, Ino.

216
00:18:54,795 --> 00:19:00,665
No matter what happens,
I won't lose to you either, Sakura!

217
00:19:06,573 --> 00:19:07,437
The ribbon...

218
00:19:07,741 --> 00:19:10,175
I'm giving back the ribbon.

219
00:19:19,954 --> 00:19:21,819
I gave you that ribbon.

220
00:19:22,423 --> 00:19:25,392
Besides, a headband is something
you put on your head, right?

221
00:19:27,227 --> 00:19:31,220
From here on, I'm no longer
a girl who will run after you, Ino.

222
00:19:32,666 --> 00:19:34,463
When I put this on my head,

223
00:19:34,568 --> 00:19:39,028
it will be as a female Shinobi
who can't lose to you.

224
00:19:51,552 --> 00:19:52,610
That's a good idea...

225
00:20:01,695 --> 00:20:02,719
Me, too...

226
00:20:04,064 --> 00:20:04,996
until that time.

227
00:20:10,137 --> 00:20:13,072
I understand... Sakura.

228
00:20:32,593 --> 00:20:33,389
- <i>This time for sure...</i>
- <i>This time for sure...</i>

229
00:20:35,396 --> 00:20:36,522
- <i>with full strength...</i>
- <i>with full strength...</i>

230
00:20:39,099 --> 00:20:42,535
- <i>a fair... fight!</i>
- <i>a fair... fight!</i>

231
00:21:06,757 --> 00:21:11,217
<i>Hey, can you hear it?</i>

232
00:21:11,294 --> 00:21:19,702
<i>The clear, blue sky goes on and on</i>

233
00:21:20,637 --> 00:21:29,306
<i>The ocean spans limitlessly</i>

234
00:21:29,746 --> 00:21:37,619
<i>Please keep that smile on your face forever</i>

235
00:21:38,889 --> 00:21:44,555
<i>Or else I'll cry</i>

236
00:21:44,628 --> 00:21:48,394
<i>You won't have to search around you</i>

237
00:21:48,465 --> 00:21:52,026
<i>It's all ok now.</i>

238
00:21:52,369 --> 00:22:00,902
<i>Everyone is inside</i>
<i>this hand</i>

239
00:22:01,178 --> 00:22:06,377
<i>when you want to cry,</i>
<i>and you want to run away</i>

240
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:10,853
<i>When you forget what happiness is</i>

241
00:22:10,921 --> 00:22:14,687
<i>Just sing.</i>

242
00:22:14,925 --> 00:22:20,090
<i>Light is born, and darkness was born</i>

243
00:22:20,163 --> 00:22:22,358
<i>The two are one</i>

244
00:22:22,466 --> 00:22:28,735
<i>Harmonia, feel the telepathy</i>

245
